This is a minimalist template for an avr-gcc project.
All files in this template are in public domain, so feel
free to use for whatever you want.

How to use this template:

Compile:
	make

Upload:
	make burn
	
Compile and upload:
	make fast

Clean output files:
	make clean

Reset the target:
	make rst

Dependencies:

This template uses by default avr-gcc to compile and link,
and avrdude to upload to the target microcontroller through
usbasp, but of course you can change it to suit your needs.

Setup instructions for Ubuntu:
	sudo apt install make avr-libc avrdude binutils-avr gcc-avr


